{
  "stem": "868.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They went around it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's when France started to fall apart.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the army, the German armies, came ever closer to Paris.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we decided to escape again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we left at the last train out of the Gare d'Austerlitz, which was the railroad station, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] joining hundreds and thousands of refugees who just fled because we saw France falling apart all around us.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And everybody went south, away from the-- from the Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we wound up in a small town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I believe we were directed there because the train could only go so far.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then when we got out, they said, well, head towards this particular village.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we went there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Very small-- I don't think it had more than a hundred people living there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we stayed there in a farmhouse that we were given [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] until it was announced that-- though I got to go back for a minute.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's while we were in that small village called Lugagnac that France capitulated.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Marechal Petain went on the radio and said, as of tomorrow, the hostilities between France and Germany are terminated.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there will be an armistice signed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This was followed by the division of France into two zones, about half and half.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The north was going to be the occupied zone, meaning that German troops were actually stationed on conquered territory, on that part of French conquered territory.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The southern part would be under the authority of the Vichy Government, headed by Petain and his prime minister, Pierre Laval.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that was going to be called the Free Zone.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
